
header:
    the statistics and analysis of gun violence in US between 2013 to 2017

    this page aims to show an intuitive facts of gun shooting in US. through providing some grsphs.

line graph:
    compared with 2013, the amount of incidents increased rapidly from 2014.Before reaching a peak in July or August(2016), the amount of victims goes through the lowest point  in February and  then flutuates slightly between 2013 and 2017.

 victims:
    According to the graph of victims, the amount of victims has increased sharply from 2013 to 2014 and reached at the top in 2016.
    The number  of injured people accounts for the largest proportion(66.3%) among the  victims. In terms of age, most of injured are adults,accounting for 91%, and teens injured takes second place, accounting for 7%.


prepetrators:
   According to the graph of  prepetrators, over 90% prepetrators is male while female only accounts for less than 10%. In terms of age,most of prepetrators are adult ,accounting for 91.86%, teen prepetrators takes sencond place for 7.76% , 0.372% of prepetrators are children ,aging  between 0 to 11.
